It recognised the <a0_0>South West Africa People's Organisation<a0_0/> (SWAPO) as the official representative of the Namibian people in <a1_0><b5_0>1973<b5_0/><a1_0/>. Namibia, however, remained under South African administration during this time as <a2_0><b6_0><b7_0>South-West<b7_0/><b6_0/> Africa.<a2_0/> Following <a3_0>internal violence<a3_0/>, South Africa installed an interim administration in Namibia in 1985.
